 point.",\n            "color_schema": {\n                "BLUE": "New input at time T",\n                "GOLD": "The evolving hidden state (memory)",\n                "GREEN": "The resulting prediction"\n            },\n            "camera_instruction": "Zoomed in on the hidden state node to show it \'absorbing\' the input.",\n            "scene_class": "ZoomedScene",\n            "duration_hint": "45s",\n            "budget": "medium",\n            "prerequisite_ids": [0],\n            "narration": "Instead of trying to look at the whole history at once, an RNN maintains a \'Hidden State\'. Think of this as a running summary. As each new piece of data arrives, the network combines it with its current summary to create a new, updated summary. It’s not storing the past; it’s being transformed by it."\n        },\n        {\n            "id": 2,\n            "title": "Unrolling the Loop",\n            "question_answered": "What does this look like over a timeline?",\n            "false_intuition_broken": "The network is a massive chain of different machines.",\n            "anchor_visual": "A single loop arrow around a node that \'unfolds\' into a repeating horizontal chain of identical structures.",\n            "anchor_position": "CENTER - Expanding from a point to a horizontal timeline.",\n            "color_schema": {\n                "BLUE": "Inputs at T, T+1, T+2",\n                "GOLD": "The recurring weight matrices (identical icons)",\n                "GRAY": "The timeline axis"\n            },\n            "camera_instruction": "Follow the \'unrolling\' motion from left to right using a camera pan.",\n            "scene_class": "MovingCameraScene",\n            "duration_hint": "40s",\n            "budget": "medium",\n            "prerequisite_ids": [1],\n            "narration": "This looks like a long chain, but here’s the secret: it’s the same network used over and over. We \'unroll\' it across time to see the flow. Because the weights—the rules for how to update the memory—are shared across every step, the RNN can process a sequence of any length using the exact same logic."\n        },\n        {\n            "id": 3,\n            "title": "The Fading Signal",\n            "question_answered": "Why do RNNs struggle with long sentences?",\n            "false_intuition_broken": "Digital memory is perfect and lasts forever.",\n            "anchor_visual": "A bright BLUE pulse at T=0 turning into a faint, ghostly GRAY flicker by T=10.",\n            "anchor_position": "LEFT to RIGHT - showing the decay across the chain.",\n            "color_schema": {\n                "BLUE": "Strong initial information",\n                "RED": "Vanishing gradient/signal loss",\n                "GRAY": "Forgotten information"\n            },\n            "camera_instruction": "Wide shot showing the entire chain, highlighting the loss of color intensity.",\n            "scene_class": "Scene",\n            "duration_hint": "30s",\n            "budget": "low",\n            "prerequisite_ids": [2],\n            "narration": "But there’s a catch. As the summary is updated again and again, the influence of the very first inputs begins to fade. In a long paragraph, the RNN might forget how the sentence started. This \'vanishing\' signal is why basic RNNs struggle with long-term dependencies, leading us to more complex architectures like LSTMs."\n        },\n        {\n            "id": 4,\n            "title": "The Sequence Engine Recap",\n            "question_answered": "What is the core takeaway of an RNN?",\n            "false_intuition_broken": "RNNs are fundamentally different from other NNs.",\n            "anchor_visual": "A 3D stack of sequence layers processing a \'wave\' of data.",\n            "anchor_position": "CENTER - 3D perspective.",\n            "color_schema": {\n                "BLUE": "Input stream",\n                "GOLD": "Shared parameters",\n                "GREEN": "Sequential output"\n            },\n            "camera_instruction": "Rotate in 3D space to show the depth of the hidden state layers.",\n            "scene_class": "ThreeDScene",\n            "duration_hint": "30s",\n            "budget": "high",\n            "prerequisite_ids": [3],\n            "narration": "In short: RNNs turn static networks into temporal ones. By sharing parameters across time and maintaining a hidden state, they transform a simple mathematical function into a machine that can \'feel\' the flow of data. They don\'t just see the world; they remember it."\n        }\n    ],\n    "transition_style": "continuation",\n    "total_duration_target": 190\n}'

